<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06291193 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06291193 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SAN-JOSE; MEN; ROBBERY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Two brothers were shot on a rural stretch of Mount Hamilton Road about 9 p.m.Wednesday by a young man who drove an off-white Buick Skylark or DodgeCharger, Santa Clara County sheriff's deputies said.;   The victims, AbelGoodvoice Elk, 24, and Frederick Goodvoice Elk, 22, were listed in stablecondition late Wednesday at San Jose Medical Center. Deputies said Frederickwas shot in the chest and Abel was grazed near his eye.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  TWO BROTHERS ROBBED, SHOT ON MOUNT HAMILTON ROAD  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     A third brother, whose name was not released, was not wounded. Police wereinterviewing him early today.;   The brothers told deputies that they hadpulled over to help another car before the assault. Deputies said the driverrobbed the brothers and shot them with a .22-caliber automatic rifle.;   Theshooting occurred near the intersection of Clayton Road and Mount HamiltonRoad, about two miles east of Alum Rock Avenue. Deputies said the brothersdrove part way down the mountain before driving off the road.;   Three peoplewere reportedly in the car with the gunman, who was described as Hispanic, inhis late teens or early 20s, 130 to 140 pounds, with long black hair combedback, a white short-sleeved shirt and blue pants.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  SCOTT HERHOLD, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911017  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  199  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday, October 17, 199100291193,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>